org.sbolstandard.core

Interface SequenceAnnotation

  • All Superinterfaces:
    SBOLObject, SBOLVisitable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SequenceAnnotationImpl
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public interface SequenceAnnotation
extends SBOLObject
    The SBOL data model's SequenceAnnotation for RDF and Json. Sequence Annotations give the location and direction of SequenceFeatures of a DnaComponent. The location is specified by the start and stop positions of the Sequence Feature along the DNA sequence. We are using the convention that the first base pair of a DNA sequence is position 1. This convention is established by the broader Molecular biology community, in literature. The direction of the feature is specified by the strand [+/-]. Sequences used are by convention assumed 5' to 3', therefore the + strand is 5' to 3' and the - strand is 3' to 5'.
